<font color="#FF0000">VIETNAM EXPERIENCES/DIALOG</font><br>
<tt>Sat May 31 19:02:55 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I would have some respect for Dr. Spatz would he had gone to prison for his beliefs and not hid behind specious drivel and diatribe.<br><br>
As a Viet Nam veteran who served in the 1st Cav Div (Airmobile) in Bien Hoa from July, 1069 to March, 1970.  My duties were varied as were my experiences.  Mortars and rockets were common disrupters of the night.  The Viet Cong and the North Vietnamese Army were of some concern but not nearly as much as during 1968.  They were decimated during the Tet Offensive and had not rebuilt themselves into effective fighting forces until after I left.  <br><br>
If Mr. McNamara is the standard for being correct, then Judas is a saint.  He never had it right.<br><br>
I am willing to communicate with anyone about my experiences in VietNam.<br><br>
Regards,<br><br>
Bill
